The '''École nationale supérieure des sciences de l'information et des bibliothèques''' (ENSSIB; French for ''National Superior School of Information Science and Libraries'') is a [[France|French]] [[university]]-level educational institution based in [[Villeurbanne]] (a borough of [[Lyon]]). It provides education and training for library curators and [[librarian]]s (already hired by the government) after a competitive examination. It also trains standards students{{clarify|date=June 2014}}, providing them a master's degree. Since 2009, the school produces the ''{{illm|Bulletin des bibliothèques de France|fr}}'' ({{issn|1292-8399}}), a journal established in 1956 by the merging of the ''Bulletin de documentation bibliographique'' and ''Bulletin d’information de la Direction des Bibliothèques de France''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://bbf.enssib.fr/histoire-du-bbf |title=Histoire du BBF |work=BBF |publisher= Ecole Nationale Superieure des Sciences de l'information et des Bibliotheques |language=fr |accessdate= 14 August 2017 }}</ref> The school belongs to the [[Couperin (consortium)|Couperin]] consortium.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.couperin.org/presentation/membres |title=Les membres de Couperin |language=fr |work=[[Couperin.org]] |accessdate= 12 July 2018 }}</ref>

